content.description: The easier choice on the front face.
content.location: The right route on the front face.  Right of American Psycho.

content.description:
An easy start passing the first two bolts leads to a hard series of moves on small pockets and a difficult third clip. From here a burly move right leads to good holds and the fourth clip. Follow easy ground past one more bolt to the anchors, 

  Really more of a boulder's route than the typical ET route. The crux moves are hard V5?, but if you like small pockets you will love this route. 

  Might be a little soft for the grade.
content.protection: 5 Bolts to an anchor with leaver biners.  There is no chain so expect your rope to get twisted.  Could use an upgrade.
content.location: The left route on the front face.  Just right of Hoggle and left of a new unknown route.

content.description: The side of the boulder facing the dirt road, this is the first wall you'll encounter from the approach trail. It has only three routes on it. The middle route is, insofar as I know, a project estimated at 5.13+
